<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-96-0686 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors investigate the high-gradient magnetic separation of magnetohydrodynamicworking fluids by magnetic separators and magnetic filters in a flowmodel depicting the convection and mass transfer aspects due to magnetodiffusionand Brownian diffusion of the colloid particles. The model is testedagainst actual experimental data for the separation behavior of magnetiteparticles suspended in kerosene or water.</TEXT></DOC>